# =============================================================================

# IMPORTANT OBSERVATIONS

# =============================================================================

#

# Observation 1

# -------------

#

# Docker Desktop automatically assigned:

#

# EXTERNAL-IP = localhost

#

# This allows local testing without configuring MetalLB.

#

#

# Observation 2

# -------------

#

# Controller Service Type:

#

# LoadBalancer

#

# Docker Desktop automatically maps it to localhost.

#

#

# Observation 3

# -------------

#

# Installing the Controller alone does NOT expose applications.

#

# The controller only waits for Ingress rules.

#

# Until an Ingress resource is created,

# the controller has no routing configuration.

#

# =============================================================================

# COMMON INGRESS

# =============================================================================

#

# Instead of creating one Ingress file per microservice,

# a single common ingress.yaml is maintained.

#

# Advantages:

#

# • Easier to manage.

# • One place for routing configuration.

# • Cleaner project structure.

# • Suitable until Spring Cloud Gateway is introduced.

#

#

# Routes configured:

#

# /orchestrator  -> ms-transaction-orchestrator

#

# /wallet        -> ms-wallet

#

# /notification  -> ms-notification

#

# =============================================================================

# HOST CONFIGURATION

# =============================================================================

#

# File:

#

# C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts

#

# Add:

#

# 127.0.0.1    msimpl.local

#

# This maps the hostname "msimpl.local" to localhost.

#

